## Overall Assessment

While the linear regression model appears to capture the general relationship between heart rate and steps, **key assumptions**—particularly constant variance and normality of errors—are <strong style="color: red;">violated</strong>. These issues suggest that inference based on this model should be interpreted with caution, and that transformations of the response variable, robust standard errors, or alternative modeling approaches may be more appropriate.

